The paper discusses the architecture of Software-Defined Cloud Computing (SDC) and its potential in optimizing cloud resources for Quality of Service (QoS) and energy efficiency. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses QoS-aware bandwidth allocation and VM placement, which are related to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of software to manage various aspects of the cloud environment falls under Software Engineering (cs.SE), and the discussion of research challenges and opportunities falls under Architecture (cs.AR).
